## ğŸš€ Steps to Run This Project

### Step 1: Install Python

Make sure you have **Python 3.13** installed on your system.
You can verify your installation by running:

```bash
python --version
Step 2: Set Up an IDE
Use any IDE of your choice for development and execution. Examples include:

Visual Studio Code

PyCharm

Jupyter Notebook (optional)

Make sure your IDE is configured to use the correct Python interpreter.

Step 3: Clone or Download the Repository
If you're using Git, clone the repository with:

Bash

git clone <repository-link>
Step 4: Navigate to the Project Directory
Change to the directory where the project files are located:

Bash

cd AI-Regulatory-Compliance-Checker
Step 5: Create and Activate a Virtual Environment
Creating a virtual environment helps manage dependencies.

For Windows (Command Prompt):
DOS

python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
For macOS / Linux:
Bash

python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
Step 6: Upgrade pip (Optional but Recommended)
Before installing packages, ensure your pip is up-to-date:

Bash

python -m pip install --upgrade pip
Step 7: Install Requirements
Install all the necessary Python dependencies listed in the requirements.txt file by running:

Bash

pip install -r requirements.txt
Step 8: Configure Environment Variables
Create a .env file in the root directory of the project and add your API keys as follows:

Code snippet

OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_key_here
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_key_here
Step 9: Run the Data Extraction Script
This script extracts text and metadata from uploaded PDF contracts.

Bash

python data_extraction.py
Step 10: Run the Streamlit Application
To launch the main web application, run:

Bash

streamlit run main.py
